edu.stanford.nlp.util
Class MetaClass

java.lang.Object
  edu.stanford.nlp.util.MetaClass

public class MetaClass
extends java.lang.Object

A meta class using Java's reflection library. Can be used to create a single instance, or a factory, where each Class from the factory share their constructor parameters.

Author:
Gabor Angeli

cast

public static final <E> E cast(java.lang.String value,
                               java.lang.reflect.Type type)
Cast a String representation of an object into that object. E.g. "5.4" will be cast to a Double; "[1,2,3]" will be cast to an Integer[]. NOTE: Date parses from a Long

Type Parameters:
E - The type of the object returned (same as type)
Parameters:
value - The string representation of the object
type - The type (usually class) to be returned (same as E)
Returns:
An object corresponding to the String value passed
